$=>$ *At least wo newspapers syndicated AI garbage* : _May 2025_ : At first glance, 'Heat index' appears as inoffensive as newspaper features get. A 'summer guide' sprawling across more than 50 pages. The feature, which was syndicated over the past week in both the Chicago Sun-Times and The Philadelphia Inquirer, contains '303 Must-Dos, Must-Tastes, and Must-Tries'. Yet, close readers of the guid noticed that something was very off. 'Heat Index' went viral when people pointed out that its guide matched real authors with books they hadn't written -- a hint that the story may have been composed by a chatbot. The author explained that he had asked the AI to help him come up with book recommendations. This time, at least, he did not actually check the chatbot's work.

