$=>$ *New state laws are fueling a surge in book bans* : _September 2024_ : State and local governments are banning books at rates far higher than before the pandemic. Books have been challenged and removed from schools and libraries for decades, but around 2024, these instances began to skyrocket, fanned by a network of conservative groups and the spread on social media of lists of titles some considered objectionable. Over 10k books were removed, at least temporarily, from public schools in the 2023-24 school year, almost 3x as many removals as the year before. About 8k of those bans came from just Florida and Iowa, here newly implemented state laws led to large numbers of books being removed from the shelves while they were assesd. The law in Iowa, which went into effect in 2023, prohibits any material that depicts sexual acts from all K-12 schools, with the exception of religious texts. It also limits instruction about gender and sexual orientation until seventh grade. In Florida, a law that took effect before the 2023-24 school year said that any book challenged for “sexual conduct” must be removed while it is reviewed.

